d":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lamont","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: from the medieval personal name <i>Lagman</i>, which is from Old Norse <i>Lǫgmathr</i>, composed of the elements <i>lǫg</i>, plural of <i>lag</i> ‘law’ (from <i>leggja</i> ‘to lay down’), + <i>mathr</i> ‘man’ (genitive <i>manns</i>).","French: habitational name, with fused definite article <i>l'</i>, from any of the places called Amont, in Haute-Saône and Haute-Vienne.","Altered form of French   Lamothe  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McClammy","meanings":["Scottish: patronymic from a pet form of   Lamont  ."]},{"name":"McClymont","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Laomuinn</b> ‘son of <i>Laomann</i>’, a personal name borrowed from Old Norse and meaning ‘law giver’. See   Lamont  ."]},{"name":"Lemond","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  .","French: variant of <b>Lemonde</b>, a nickname from Old French <i>monde</i> ‘pure’, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>.","French (<b>Lémond</b>): variant of <b>Laymond</b>, itself a variant, with fused definite article <i>l'</i>, of   Aymond  ."]},{"name":"Lemont","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  .","French: habitational name from Le Mont in the Vosges or possibly other minor places so named from Old French <i>mont</i> ‘mountain’. Alternatively, a variant of   Lemond   2."]},{"name":"Lemonds","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  , with English excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Lawman","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Lamont  .","English: occupational name from Middle English <i>lagman</i>, <i>lagheman</i> ‘law-man, one whose duty is to declare the law; lawyer’ (Old Norse <i>lagmann-</i>, <i>lǫgmann-</i>, oblique case of <i>lǫgmathr</i>). The word was also widely used as a personal name, Middle English <i>Lagman</i>, <i>Lagheman</i>."]},{"name":"Lamond","meanings":["Scottish, northern Irish, and French: variant of   Lamont  . This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Lamothe","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Jacques, Pierre, Donat, Francois, Lucien, Odette, Adrien, Andree, Armand, Armande.","French: variant of   Lamotte  , or a habitational name from any of the places in France named Lamothe or La Mothe.","History: The settlement that became the city of Detroit was founded in 1701 by Antoine de la Mothe, Sieur de Cadillac (1658–1730), governor of LA. He was born into the minor nobility in Gascony, France, where his father owned the seigneury of Cadillac."]},{"name":"Lamonte","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  ."]}]},{"name":"Malcolm","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the medieval Gaelic name <i>Mael Coluim</i> ‘devotee of St Columba’. Columba was a 6th-century monk of Irish origin who played a leading part in the conversion to Christianity of Scotland and northern England;  see also  Callum   and   Colm .  He has always been one of the most popular saints in Scotland, but in the Middle Ages it was felt to be presumptuous to give the names of saints directly to children; instead their blessing was invoked by prefixing the name with <i>mael</i> ‘devotee of’ or <i>gille</i> ‘servant of’. Since the 1930s the given name has been used widely in the English-speaking world, not just by those with Scottish connections."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Malcolm Lamont 2nd Chief of Clan Lamont was born in 1250, in Lamont, Argyll, Scotland, his father, Laumon Lamont 1st Chief of Clan Lamont, was 16 and his mother, Lady Jean de Lyons, was 35. He married Lady Christina Macdougall on 26 September 1290, in Argyll, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1294, in Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland, at the age of 44, and was buried in Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland."},"et":{"1250–1294":"1250–1294","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1290–1353":"1290–1353","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1353":"1353","1265":"1265","26 September 1290":"26. september 1290","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","Lorne, Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Lochowe, Argyllshire, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"1250–1294":"1250–1294","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1290–1353":"1290–1353","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1290":"noin 1290","1353":"1353","1265":"1265","26 September 1290":"26. syyskuuta 1290","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","Lorne, Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Lochowe, Argyllshire, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"1250–1294":"1250–1294","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1290–1353":"1290–1353","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Décédée","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1290":"environ 1290","1353":"1353","1265":"1265","26 September 1290":"26 septembre 1290","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","Lorne, Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Écosse","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Écosse","Lochowe, Argyllshire, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilfinan, Argyll, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Malcolm Lamont 2nd Chief of Clan Lamont est né en 1250, à Lamont, Argyll, Écosse, son père, Laumon Lamont 1st Chief of Clan Lamont, avait 16 ans et sa mère, Lady Jean de Lyons, avait 35 ans. Il a épousé Lady Christina Macdougall le 26 septembre 1290, à Argyll, Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1294, à Kilfinan, Argyll, Écosse, à l’âge de 44 ans, et a été enterré à Kilfinan, Argyll, Écosse."},"de":{"1250–1294":"1250–1294","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1290–1353":"1290–1353","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Verstorben","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1290":"um 1290","1353":"1353","1265":"1265","26 September 1290":"26. September 1290","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","Lorne, Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Lochowe, Argyllshire, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Schottland, United Kingdom","Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Schottland, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Als Malcolm Lamont 2nd Chief of Clan Lamont 1250 in Lamont, Argyll, Scotland geboren wurde, war sein Vater Laumon Lamont 1st Chief of Clan Lamont 16 und seine Mutter Lady Jean de Lyons 35. Er hat am 26. September 1290 in Argyll, Scotland Lady Christina Macdougall geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1294 im Alter von 44 Jahren in Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland und wurde in Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"1250–1294":"1250–1294","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1290–1353":"1290–1353","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Desede","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1290":"about 1290","1353":"1353","1265":"1265","26 September 1290":"26 September 1290","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","Lorne, Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Lochowe, Argyllshire, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Ecosse, United Kingdom","Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilfinan, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Ecosse, United Kingdom","Argyll